subject: Re: [junit] JUnit Talk in Dallas
msgSnippet: Mike, We have several prospects and lots of friends in Dallas.  I think listening to what you have to say should be strongly recommended!  How can we help?
messageBody:
Mike,
We have several prospects and lots of friends in Dallas. I think listening to what you have to say should be strongly recommended! How can we help? Can anyone attend?

----- Original Message -----
From: Mike Clark
Sent: Friday, April 19, 2002 5:44 PM
To: junit@yahoogroups.com
Subject: [junit] JUnit Talk in Dallas

I'm giving a talk on JUnit next month at the Lone Star Software
Symposium in Dallas, TX. Giddy-up!

The presentation is a technical primer to using JUnit and the techniques
of test-first design. It also covers examples uses of Ant, Cactus,
HttpUnit, and JUnitPerf, among others.

If anyone in the Dallas area is interested, email me privately for
details. It would be great to meet some folks on this list.

Thanks,

Mike
